018 film)|The Heiresses]]'' || ''Las herederas'' || {{flagu|Paraguay}} ||<ref>{{cite web|title=68th Berlin International Film Festival \u2013 Silver Bear for Best Actress|url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/2018/03_preistraeger_2018/03_preistraeger_2018.html|publisher=Internationale Filmfestspiele Berlin|accessdate=10 December 2018|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223140740/https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/2018/03_preistraeger_2018/03_preistraeger_2018.html|archivedate=23 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[69th Berlin International Film Festival|2019]] ||data-sort-value=\"Yong\"| [[Yong Mei]] || Wang Liyun || data-sort-value=\"So\" | ''[[So Long, My Son]]'' || ''\u5730\u4e45\u5929\u957f'' || {{flagu|China}} ||<ref>{{cite web|title=69th Berlin International Film Festival \u2013 Silver Bear for Best Actress|url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/2019/03_preistraeger_2019/03_preistraeger_2019.html|publisher=Internationale Filmfestspiele Berlin|accessdate=17 February 2020|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191116163628/https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/2019/03_preistraeger_2019/03_preistraeger_2019.html|archivedate=16 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| colspan=7 data-sort-value=\"\u03c9\" style=\"background-color:#EAECF0; font-weight:bold; padding-left:20%\"| 2020s\n|-\n| [[70th Berlin International Film Festival|2020]] ||data-sort-value=\"Yong\"| [[Paula Beer]] || Undine Wibeau || colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Undine\" | ''[[Undine (2020 film)|Undine]]'' || {{flagu|Germany}} ||<ref>{{cite web|title=70th Berlin International Film Festival \u2013 Silver Bear for Best Actress|url=https://www.berlinale.de/media/service-2020/berlinale-awards-2020.pdf|publisher=Internationale Filmfestspiele Berlin|accessdate=29 February 2020}}</ref> \n|-\n|}\n\n==Multiple award winners==\n\n'''2 awards'''\n* [[Shirley MacLaine]] (USA) \u2013 ''[[Ask Any Girl (film)|Ask Any Girl]]'' (1959), ''[[Desperate Characters]]'' (1971)\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cannes Film Festival Award for Best Actress]]\n* [[Volpi Cup for Best Actress]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons|Berlinale}}\n* [http://www.berlinale.de Berlinale website]\n* [https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000091/2015 Berlin Film Festival at IMDb]\n\n{{Silver Bear for Best Actress}}\n{{Berlin International Film Festival}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Silver Bear For Best Actress}}\n[[Category:Berlin International Film Festival]]\n[[Category:Silver Bear for Best Actress winners| ]]\n[[Category:Film awards for lead actress]]\n[[Category:Awards for actresses]]\n[[Category:Lists of films by award|Silver Bear, Best Actress]]\n", "text_old": "The '''Silver Bear for Best Actress''' ({{lang-de|Silberner B\u00e4r/Beste Darstellerin}}) is the [[Berlin International Film Festival]]'s award for achievement in performance by an [[actress]]. It is selected by the jury of the festival for films in the official competition slate. \n\nThe award was first presented in 1956, and can be for lead or supporting roles. The award was not presented in 1969, 1970, 1973, 1974, and 1990. [[Sachiko Hidari]] is the only actress who won the award for two films in the 1964 competition. In 2011, the award was given to the entire female cast of ''[[A Separation]]''. [[Shirley MacLaine]] is the only actress that has won the award more than once.\n\n==Award winners==\n[[File:Elsa Martinelli 1964.JPG|thumb|150px|alt= photo of Elsa Martinelli|[[Elsa Martinelli]], the first winner of the Berlin Film Festival Award for Best Actress.]][[File:Elizabeth Taylor-1954.JPG|thumb|150px|alt= photo of Elizabeth Taylor|[[Elizabeth Taylor]], winner of the 1972 Berlin Film Festival Award for Best Actress.]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ Table key\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"height:20px; width:30px\" | \u2020\n| Indicates the performance was also an [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]] '''winner'''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" style=\"height:20px; width:30px\" | \u2021 \n| Indicates the performance was also '''nominated''' for an [[Academy Awards|Academy Award]]\n|-\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Actress !! Role !! Film !! Original title !! Nationality of actress !! Ref.\n|-\n| colspan=7 data-sort-value=\"\u03c9\" style=\"background-color:#EAECF0; font-weight:bold; padding-left:20%\"| 1950s\n|-\n| [[6th Berlin International Film Festival|1956]] ||data-sort-value=\"Martinelli\"| [[Elsa Martinelli]] || Donatella || colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Donatella\" | ''[[Donatella (film)|Donatella]]'' || {{flagu|Italy}} ||<ref>{{cite web|title=6th Berlin International Film Festival \u2013 Silver Bear for Best Actress|url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/1956/03_preistraeger_1956/03_Preistraeger_1956.html|publisher=Internationale Filmfestspiele Berlin|accessdate=10 December 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223140530/https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/1956/03_preistraeger_1956/03_preistraeger_1956.html|archivedate=23 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[7th Berlin International Film Festival|1957]] ||data-sort-value=\"Mitchell\"| [[Yvonne Mitchell]] || Amy Preston || colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Woman\" | ''[[Woman in a Dressing Gown]]'' || {{flagu|United Kingdom}} ||<ref>{{cite web|title=7th Berlin International Film Festival \u2013 Silver Bear for Best Actress|url=https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/1957/03_preistraeger_1957/03_Preistraeger_1957.html|publisher=Internationale Filmfestspiele Berlin|accessdate=10 December 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223140531/https://www.berlinale.de/en/archive/jahresarchive/1957/03_preistraeger_1957/03_preistraeger_1957.html|archivedate=23 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[8th Berlin International Film Festival|1958]] ||data-sort-value=\"Magnani\"| [[Anna Magnani]] || Gioia \u2021 || colspan=2 data-sort-value=\"Wild\" | ''[[Wild Is the Wind]]'' || {{flagu|Italy}} ||<ref>{{cite web|title=8th Berlin International Film Festival \u2013 